36using Assembler = TARGET_ASSEMBLER;
37class Reg;
38
39class MacroAssemblerARM64 : public AbstractMacroAssembler<Assembler> {
40public:
41 static constexpr unsigned numGPRs = 32;
42 static constexpr unsigned numFPRs = 32;
43
44 static constexpr RegisterID dataTempRegister = ARM64Registers::ip0;
45 static constexpr RegisterID memoryTempRegister = ARM64Registers::ip1;
46
47 static constexpr RegisterID InvalidGPRReg = ARM64Registers::InvalidGPRReg;
48
49 RegisterID scratchRegister()
50 {
51 RELEASE_ASSERT(m_allowScratchRegister);
52 return getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate();
53 }
54
55protected:
56 static constexpr ARM64Registers::FPRegisterID fpTempRegister = ARM64Registers::q31;
57 static constexpr Assembler::SetFlags S = Assembler::S;
58 static constexpr int64_t maskHalfWord0 = 0xffffl;
59 static constexpr int64_t maskHalfWord1 = 0xffff0000l;
60 static constexpr int64_t maskUpperWord = 0xffffffff00000000l;
61
62 static constexpr size_t INSTRUCTION_SIZE = 4;
63
64 // N instructions to load the pointer + 1 call instruction.
65 static constexpr ptrdiff_t REPATCH_OFFSET_CALL_TO_POINTER = -((Assembler::MAX_POINTER_BITS / 16 + 1) * INSTRUCTION_SIZE);
66
67public:
68 MacroAssemblerARM64()
69 : m_dataMemoryTempRegister(this, dataTempRegister)
70 , m_cachedMemoryTempRegister(this, memoryTempRegister)
71 , m_makeJumpPatchable(false)
72 {
73 }
74
75 typedef Assembler::LinkRecord LinkRecord;
76 typedef Assembler::JumpType JumpType;
77 typedef Assembler::JumpLinkType JumpLinkType;
78 typedef Assembler::Condition Condition;
79
80 static constexpr Assembler::Condition DefaultCondition = Assembler::ConditionInvalid;
81 static constexpr Assembler::JumpType DefaultJump = Assembler::JumpNoConditionFixedSize;
82
83 Vector<LinkRecord, 0, UnsafeVectorOverflow>& jumpsToLink() { return m_assembler.jumpsToLink(); }
84 static bool canCompact(JumpType jumpType) { return Assembler::canCompact(jumpType); }
85 static JumpLinkType computeJumpType(JumpType jumpType, const uint8_t* from, const uint8_t* to) { return Assembler::computeJumpType(jumpType, from, to); }
86 static JumpLinkType computeJumpType(LinkRecord& record, const uint8_t* from, const uint8_t* to) { return Assembler::computeJumpType(record, from, to); }
87 static int jumpSizeDelta(JumpType jumpType, JumpLinkType jumpLinkType) { return Assembler::jumpSizeDelta(jumpType, jumpLinkType); }
88
89 template <Assembler::CopyFunction copy>
90 ALWAYS_INLINE static void link(LinkRecord& record, uint8_t* from, const uint8_t* fromInstruction, uint8_t* to) { return Assembler::link<copy>(record, from, fromInstruction, to); }
91
92 static bool isCompactPtrAlignedAddressOffset(ptrdiff_t value)
93 {
94 // This is the largest 32-bit access allowed, aligned to 64-bit boundary.
95 return !(value & ~0x3ff8);
96 }
97
98 enum RelationalCondition {
99 Equal = Assembler::ConditionEQ,
100 NotEqual = Assembler::ConditionNE,
101 Above = Assembler::ConditionHI,
102 AboveOrEqual = Assembler::ConditionHS,
103 Below = Assembler::ConditionLO,
104 BelowOrEqual = Assembler::ConditionLS,
105 GreaterThan = Assembler::ConditionGT,
106 GreaterThanOrEqual = Assembler::ConditionGE,
107 LessThan = Assembler::ConditionLT,
108 LessThanOrEqual = Assembler::ConditionLE
109 };
110
111 enum ResultCondition {
112 Overflow = Assembler::ConditionVS,
113 Signed = Assembler::ConditionMI,
114 PositiveOrZero = Assembler::ConditionPL,
115 Zero = Assembler::ConditionEQ,
116 NonZero = Assembler::ConditionNE
117 };
118
119 enum ZeroCondition {
120 IsZero = Assembler::ConditionEQ,
121 IsNonZero = Assembler::ConditionNE
122 };
123
124 enum DoubleCondition {
125 // These conditions will only evaluate to true if the comparison is ordered - i.e. neither operand is NaN.
126 DoubleEqualAndOrdered = Assembler::ConditionEQ,
127 DoubleNotEqualAndOrdered = Assembler::ConditionVC, // Not the right flag! check for this & handle differently.
128 DoubleGreaterThanAndOrdered = Assembler::ConditionGT,
129 DoubleGreaterThanOrEqualAndOrdered = Assembler::ConditionGE,
130 DoubleLessThanAndOrdered = Assembler::ConditionLO,
131 DoubleLessThanOrEqualAndOrdered = Assembler::ConditionLS,
132 // If either operand is NaN, these conditions always evaluate to true.
133 DoubleEqualOrUnordered = Assembler::ConditionVS, // Not the right flag! check for this & handle differently.
134 DoubleNotEqualOrUnordered = Assembler::ConditionNE,
135 DoubleGreaterThanOrUnordered = Assembler::ConditionHI,
136 DoubleGreaterThanOrEqualOrUnordered = Assembler::ConditionHS,
137 DoubleLessThanOrUnordered = Assembler::ConditionLT,
138 DoubleLessThanOrEqualOrUnordered = Assembler::ConditionLE,
139 };

142 static constexpr RegisterID framePointerRegister = ARM64Registers::fp;
143 static constexpr RegisterID linkRegister = ARM64Registers::lr;

149 // Integer operations:
150
151 void add32(RegisterID a, RegisterID b, RegisterID dest)
152 {
153 ASSERT(a != ARM64Registers::sp || b != ARM64Registers::sp);
154 if (b == ARM64Registers::sp)
155 std::swap(a, b);
156 m_assembler.add<32>(dest, a, b);
157 }
158
159 void add32(RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
160 {
161 if (src == ARM64Registers::sp)
162 m_assembler.add<32>(dest, src, dest);
163 else
164 m_assembler.add<32>(dest, dest, src);
165 }
166
167 void add32(TrustedImm32 imm, RegisterID dest)
168 {
169 add32(imm, dest, dest);
170 }
171
172 void add32(TrustedImm32 imm, RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
173 {
174 if (isUInt12(imm.m_value))
175 m_assembler.add<32>(dest, src, UInt12(imm.m_value));
176 else if (isUInt12(-imm.m_value))
177 m_assembler.sub<32>(dest, src, UInt12(-imm.m_value));
178 else if (src != dest) {
179 move(imm, dest);
180 add32(src, dest);
181 } else {
182 move(imm, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
183 m_assembler.add<32>(dest, src, dataTempRegister);
184 }
185 }
186
187 void add32(TrustedImm32 imm, Address address)
188 {
189 load32(address, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
190
191 if (isUInt12(imm.m_value))
192 m_assembler.add<32>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(imm.m_value));
193 else if (isUInt12(-imm.m_value))
194 m_assembler.sub<32>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(-imm.m_value));
195 else {
196 move(imm, getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
197 m_assembler.add<32>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, memoryTempRegister);
198 }
199
200 store32(dataTempRegister, address);
201 }
202
203 void add32(TrustedImm32 imm, AbsoluteAddress address)
204 {
205 load32(address.m_ptr, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
206
207 if (isUInt12(imm.m_value)) {
208 m_assembler.add<32>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(imm.m_value));
209 store32(dataTempRegister, address.m_ptr);
210 return;
211 }
212
213 if (isUInt12(-imm.m_value)) {
214 m_assembler.sub<32>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(-imm.m_value));
215 store32(dataTempRegister, address.m_ptr);
216 return;
217 }
218
219 move(imm, getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
220 m_assembler.add<32>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, memoryTempRegister);
221 store32(dataTempRegister, address.m_ptr);
222 }
223
224 void add32(Address src, RegisterID dest)
225 {
226 load32(src, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
227 add32(dataTempRegister, dest);
228 }
229
230 void add32(AbsoluteAddress src, RegisterID dest)
231 {
232 load32(src.m_ptr, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
233 add32(dataTempRegister, dest);
234 }
235
236 void add64(RegisterID a, RegisterID b, RegisterID dest)
237 {
238 ASSERT(a != ARM64Registers::sp || b != ARM64Registers::sp);
239 if (b == ARM64Registers::sp)
240 std::swap(a, b);
241 m_assembler.add<64>(dest, a, b);
242 }
243
244 void add64(RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
245 {
246 if (src == ARM64Registers::sp)
247 m_assembler.add<64>(dest, src, dest);
248 else
249 m_assembler.add<64>(dest, dest, src);
250 }
251
252 void add64(TrustedImm32 imm, RegisterID dest)
253 {
254 if (isUInt12(imm.m_value)) {
255 m_assembler.add<64>(dest, dest, UInt12(imm.m_value));
256 return;
257 }
258 if (isUInt12(-imm.m_value)) {
259 m_assembler.sub<64>(dest, dest, UInt12(-imm.m_value));
260 return;
261 }
262
263 signExtend32ToPtr(imm, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
264 m_assembler.add<64>(dest, dest, dataTempRegister);
265 }
266
267 void add64(TrustedImm64 imm, RegisterID dest)
268 {
269 intptr_t immediate = imm.m_value;
270
271 if (isUInt12(immediate)) {
272 m_assembler.add<64>(dest, dest, UInt12(static_cast<int32_t>(immediate)));
273 return;
274 }
275 if (isUInt12(-immediate)) {
276 m_assembler.sub<64>(dest, dest, UInt12(static_cast<int32_t>(-immediate)));
277 return;
278 }
279
280 move(imm, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
281 m_assembler.add<64>(dest, dest, dataTempRegister);
282 }
283
284 void add64(TrustedImm32 imm, RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
285 {
286 if (isUInt12(imm.m_value)) {
287 m_assembler.add<64>(dest, src, UInt12(imm.m_value));
288 return;
289 }
290 if (isUInt12(-imm.m_value)) {
291 m_assembler.sub<64>(dest, src, UInt12(-imm.m_value));
292 return;
293 }
294
295 signExtend32ToPtr(imm, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
296 m_assembler.add<64>(dest, src, dataTempRegister);
297 }
298
299 void add64(TrustedImm32 imm, Address address)
300 {
301 load64(address, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
302
303 if (isUInt12(imm.m_value))
304 m_assembler.add<64>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(imm.m_value));
305 else if (isUInt12(-imm.m_value))
306 m_assembler.sub<64>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(-imm.m_value));
307 else {
308 signExtend32ToPtr(imm, getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
309 m_assembler.add<64>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, memoryTempRegister);
310 }
311
312 store64(dataTempRegister, address);
313 }
314
315 void add64(TrustedImm32 imm, AbsoluteAddress address)
316 {
317 load64(address.m_ptr, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
318
319 if (isUInt12(imm.m_value)) {
320 m_assembler.add<64>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(imm.m_value));
321 store64(dataTempRegister, address.m_ptr);
322 return;
323 }
324
325 if (isUInt12(-imm.m_value)) {
326 m_assembler.sub<64>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(-imm.m_value));
327 store64(dataTempRegister, address.m_ptr);
328 return;
329 }
330
331 signExtend32ToPtr(imm, getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
332 m_assembler.add<64>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, memoryTempRegister);
333 store64(dataTempRegister, address.m_ptr);
334 }

353 void and32(RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
354 {
355 and32(dest, src, dest);

358 void and32(RegisterID op1, RegisterID op2, RegisterID dest)
359 {
360 m_assembler.and_<32>(dest, op1, op2);
361 }
362
363 void and32(TrustedImm32 imm, RegisterID dest)
364 {
365 and32(imm, dest, dest);
366 }
367
368 void and32(TrustedImm32 imm, RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
369 {
370 LogicalImmediate logicalImm = LogicalImmediate::create32(imm.m_value);
371
372 if (logicalImm.isValid()) {
373 m_assembler.and_<32>(dest, src, logicalImm);
374 return;
375 }
376
377 move(imm, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
378 m_assembler.and_<32>(dest, src, dataTempRegister);
379 }
380
381 void and32(Address src, RegisterID dest)
382 {
383 load32(src, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
384 and32(dataTempRegister, dest);
385 }
386
387 void and16(Address src, RegisterID dest)
388 {
389 load16(src, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
390 and32(dataTempRegister, dest);
391 }

394 {
395 m_assembler.and_<64>(dest, src1, src2);
396 }

398 void and64(TrustedImm64 imm, RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
399 {
400 LogicalImmediate logicalImm = LogicalImmediate::create64(imm.m_value);
401
402 if (logicalImm.isValid()) {
403 m_assembler.and_<64>(dest, src, logicalImm);
404 return;
405 }

409 }
410
411 void and64(RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
412 {
413 m_assembler.and_<64>(dest, dest, src);
414 }
415
416 void and64(TrustedImm32 imm, RegisterID dest)
417 {
418 LogicalImmediate logicalImm = LogicalImmediate::create64(static_cast<intptr_t>(static_cast<int64_t>(imm.m_value)));
419
420 if (logicalImm.isValid()) {
421 m_assembler.and_<64>(dest, dest, logicalImm);
422 return;
423 }
424
425 signExtend32ToPtr(imm, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
426 m_assembler.and_<64>(dest, dest, dataTempRegister);
427 }
428
429 void and64(TrustedImmPtr imm, RegisterID dest)
430 {
431 intptr_t value = imm.asIntptr();
432 if constexpr (sizeof(void*) == sizeof(uint64_t))
433 and64(TrustedImm64(value), dest);
434 else
435 and64(TrustedImm32(static_cast<int32_t>(value)), dest);
436 }
437
438 void and64(TrustedImm64 imm, RegisterID dest)
439 {
440 LogicalImmediate logicalImm = LogicalImmediate::create64(bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(imm.m_value));
441
442 if (logicalImm.isValid()) {
443 m_assembler.and_<64>(dest, dest, logicalImm);
444 return;
445 }
446
447 move(imm, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
448 m_assembler.and_<64>(dest, dest, dataTempRegister);
449 }

552 void clearBit64(RegisterID bitToClear, RegisterID dest, RegisterID scratchForMask = InvalidGPRReg)
553 {
554 if (scratchForMask == InvalidGPRReg)
555 scratchForMask = scratchRegister();
556
557 move(TrustedImm32(1), scratchForMask);
558 lshift64(bitToClear, scratchForMask);
559 clearBits64WithMask(scratchForMask, dest);
560 }
561
562 enum class ClearBitsAttributes {
563 OKToClobberMask,
564 MustPreserveMask
565 };

567 void clearBits64WithMask(RegisterID mask, RegisterID dest, ClearBitsAttributes = ClearBitsAttributes::OKToClobberMask)
568 {
569 clearBits64WithMask(dest, mask, dest);
570 }

572 void clearBits64WithMask(RegisterID src, RegisterID mask, RegisterID dest, ClearBitsAttributes = ClearBitsAttributes::OKToClobberMask)
573 {
574 m_assembler.bic<64>(dest, src, mask);
575 }

577 void countLeadingZeros32(RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
578 {
579 m_assembler.clz<32>(dest, src);
580 }
581
582 void countLeadingZeros64(RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
583 {
584 m_assembler.clz<64>(dest, src);
585 }
586
587 void countTrailingZeros32(RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
588 {
589 // Arm does not have a count trailing zeros only a count leading zeros.
590 m_assembler.rbit<32>(dest, src);
591 m_assembler.clz<32>(dest, dest);
592 }
593
594 void countTrailingZeros64(RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
595 {
596 // Arm does not have a count trailing zeros only a count leading zeros.
597 m_assembler.rbit<64>(dest, src);
598 m_assembler.clz<64>(dest, dest);
599 }
600
601 void countTrailingZeros64WithoutNullCheck(RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
602 {
603#if ASSERT_ENABLED
604 Jump notZero = branchTest64(NonZero, src);
605 abortWithReason(MacroAssemblerOops, __LINE__);
606 notZero.link(this);
607#endif
608 // Arm did not need an explicit null check to begin with. So, we can do
609 // exactly the same thing as in countTrailingZeros64().
610 countTrailingZeros64(src, dest);
611 }

1010 void sub32(RegisterID left, TrustedImm32 imm, RegisterID dest)
1011 {
1012 intptr_t immediate = imm.m_value;
1013
1014 if (isUInt12(immediate)) {
1015 m_assembler.sub<32>(dest, left, UInt12(immediate));
1016 return;
1017 }
1018 if (isUInt12(-immediate)) {
1019 m_assembler.add<32>(dest, left, UInt12(-immediate));
1020 return;
1021 }
1022
1023 move(imm, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
1024 m_assembler.sub<32>(dest, left, dataTempRegister);
1025 }

1027 void sub32(TrustedImm32 imm, Address address)
1028 {
1029 load32(address, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
1030
1031 if (isUInt12(imm.m_value))
1032 m_assembler.sub<32>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(imm.m_value));
1033 else if (isUInt12(-imm.m_value))
1034 m_assembler.add<32>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(-imm.m_value));
1035 else {
1036 move(imm, getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
1037 m_assembler.sub<32>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, memoryTempRegister);
1038 }
1039
1040 store32(dataTempRegister, address);
1041 }
1042
1043 void sub32(TrustedImm32 imm, AbsoluteAddress address)
1044 {
1045 load32(address.m_ptr, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
1046
1047 if (isUInt12(imm.m_value)) {
1048 m_assembler.sub<32>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(imm.m_value));
1049 store32(dataTempRegister, address.m_ptr);
1050 return;
1051 }
1052
1053 if (isUInt12(-imm.m_value)) {
1054 m_assembler.add<32>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(-imm.m_value));
1055 store32(dataTempRegister, address.m_ptr);
1056 return;
1057 }
1058
1059 move(imm, getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
1060 m_assembler.sub<32>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, memoryTempRegister);
1061 store32(dataTempRegister, address.m_ptr);
1062 }

1291 void load64(ImplicitAddress address, RegisterID dest)
1292 {
1293 if (tryLoadWithOffset<64>(dest, address.base, address.offset))
1294 return;
1295
1296 signExtend32ToPtr(TrustedImm32(address.offset), getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
1297 m_assembler.ldr<64>(dest, address.base, memoryTempRegister);
1298 }
1299
1300 void load64(BaseIndex address, RegisterID dest)
1301 {
1302 if (!address.offset && (!address.scale || address.scale == 3)) {
1303 m_assembler.ldr<64>(dest, address.base, address.index, Assembler::UXTX, address.scale);
1304 return;
1305 }
1306
1307 signExtend32ToPtr(TrustedImm32(address.offset), getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
1308 m_assembler.add<64>(memoryTempRegister, memoryTempRegister, address.index, Assembler::UXTX, address.scale);
1309 m_assembler.ldr<64>(dest, address.base, memoryTempRegister);
1310 }

1322 DataLabel32 load64WithAddressOffsetPatch(Address address, RegisterID dest)

1324 DataLabel32 label(this);
1325 signExtend32ToPtrWithFixedWidth(address.offset, getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
1326 m_assembler.ldr<64>(dest, address.base, memoryTempRegister, Assembler::SXTW, 0);
1327 return label;
1328 }

1330 DataLabelCompact load64WithCompactAddressOffsetPatch(Address address, RegisterID dest)
1331 {
1332 ASSERT(isCompactPtrAlignedAddressOffset(address.offset));
1333 DataLabelCompact label(this);
1334 m_assembler.ldr<64>(dest, address.base, address.offset);
1335 return label;
1336 }

1367
1368 void abortWithReason(AbortReason reason)
1369 {
1370 // It is safe to use dataTempRegister directly since this is a crashing JIT Assert.
1371 move(TrustedImm32(reason), dataTempRegister);
1372 breakpoint();
1373 }

1375 void abortWithReason(AbortReason reason, intptr_t misc)
1376 {
1377 // It is safe to use memoryTempRegister directly since this is a crashing JIT Assert.
1378 move(TrustedImm64(misc), memoryTempRegister);
1379 abortWithReason(reason);
1380 }

1978 // Convert 'src' to an integer, and places the resulting 'dest'.
1979 // If the result is not representable as a 32 bit value, branch.
1980 // May also branch for some values that are representable in 32 bits
1981 // (specifically, in this case, 0).
1982 void branchConvertDoubleToInt32(FPRegisterID src, RegisterID dest, JumpList& failureCases, FPRegisterID, bool negZeroCheck = true)
1983 {
1984 m_assembler.fcvtns<32, 64>(dest, src);
1985
1986 // Convert the integer result back to float & compare to the original value - if not equal or unordered (NaN) then jump.
1987 m_assembler.scvtf<64, 32>(fpTempRegister, dest);
1988 failureCases.append(branchDouble(DoubleNotEqualOrUnordered, src, fpTempRegister));
1989
1990 // Test for negative zero.
1991 if (negZeroCheck) {
1992 Jump valueIsNonZero = branchTest32(NonZero, dest);
1993 RegisterID scratch = getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate();
1994 m_assembler.fmov<64>(scratch, src);
1995 failureCases.append(makeTestBitAndBranch(scratch, 63, IsNonZero));
1996 valueIsNonZero.link(this);
1997 }
1998 }
1999
2000 Jump branchDouble(DoubleCondition cond, FPRegisterID left, FPRegisterID right)
2001 {
2002 m_assembler.fcmp<64>(left, right);
2003 return jumpAfterFloatingPointCompare(cond);
2004 }
2005
2006 Jump branchFloat(DoubleCondition cond, FPRegisterID left, FPRegisterID right)
2007 {
2008 m_assembler.fcmp<32>(left, right);
2009 return jumpAfterFloatingPointCompare(cond);
2010 }

2016 });

2023 });

2026 Jump branchDoubleNonZero(FPRegisterID reg, FPRegisterID)
2027 {
2028 m_assembler.fcmp_0<64>(reg);
2029 Jump unordered = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionVS);
2030 Jump result = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionNE);
2031 unordered.link(this);
2032 return result;
2033 }
2034
2035 Jump branchDoubleZeroOrNaN(FPRegisterID reg, FPRegisterID)
2036 {
2037 m_assembler.fcmp_0<64>(reg);
2038 Jump unordered = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionVS);
2039 Jump notEqual = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionNE);
2040 unordered.link(this);
2041 // We get here if either unordered or equal.
2042 Jump result = jump();
2043 notEqual.link(this);
2044 return result;
2045 }
2046
2047 Jump branchTruncateDoubleToInt32(FPRegisterID src, RegisterID dest, BranchTruncateType branchType = BranchIfTruncateFailed)
2048 {
2049 // Truncate to a 64-bit integer in dataTempRegister, copy the low 32-bit to dest.
2050 m_assembler.fcvtzs<64, 64>(getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate(), src);
2051 zeroExtend32ToWord(dataTempRegister, dest);
2052 // Check the low 32-bits sign extend to be equal to the full value.
2053 m_assembler.cmp<64>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, Assembler::SXTW, 0);
2054 return Jump(makeBranch(branchType == BranchIfTruncateSuccessful ? Equal : NotEqual));
2055 }

2238 template<int datasize>
2239 void moveConditionallyAfterFloatingPointCompare(DoubleCondition cond, RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
2240 {
2241 if (cond == DoubleNotEqualAndOrdered) {
2242 Jump unordered = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionVS);
2243 m_assembler.csel<datasize>(dest, src, dest, Assembler::ConditionNE);
2244 unordered.link(this);
2245 return;
2246 }
2247 if (cond == DoubleEqualOrUnordered) {
2248 // If the compare is unordered, src is copied to dest and the
2249 // next csel has all arguments equal to src.
2250 // If the compare is ordered, dest is unchanged and EQ decides
2251 // what value to set.
2252 m_assembler.csel<datasize>(dest, src, dest, Assembler::ConditionVS);
2253 m_assembler.csel<datasize>(dest, src, dest, Assembler::ConditionEQ);
2254 return;
2255 }
2256 m_assembler.csel<datasize>(dest, src, dest, ARM64Condition(cond));
2257 }
2258
2259 template<int datasize>
2260 void moveConditionallyAfterFloatingPointCompare(DoubleCondition cond, RegisterID thenCase, RegisterID elseCase, RegisterID dest)
2261 {
2262 if (cond == DoubleNotEqualAndOrdered) {
2263 if (dest == thenCase) {
2264 // If the compare is unordered, elseCase is copied to thenCase and the
2265 // next csel has all arguments equal to elseCase.
2266 // If the compare is ordered, dest is unchanged and NE decides
2267 // what value to set.
2268 m_assembler.csel<datasize>(thenCase, elseCase, thenCase, Assembler::ConditionVS);
2269 m_assembler.csel<datasize>(dest, thenCase, elseCase, Assembler::ConditionNE);
2270 } else {
2271 move(elseCase, dest);
2272 Jump unordered = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionVS);
2273 m_assembler.csel<datasize>(dest, thenCase, elseCase, Assembler::ConditionNE);
2274 unordered.link(this);
2275 }
2276 return;
2277 }
2278 if (cond == DoubleEqualOrUnordered) {
2279 if (dest == elseCase) {
2280 // If the compare is unordered, thenCase is copied to elseCase and the
2281 // next csel has all arguments equal to thenCase.
2282 // If the compare is ordered, dest is unchanged and EQ decides
2283 // what value to set.
2284 m_assembler.csel<datasize>(elseCase, thenCase, elseCase, Assembler::ConditionVS);
2285 m_assembler.csel<datasize>(dest, thenCase, elseCase, Assembler::ConditionEQ);
2286 } else {
2287 move(thenCase, dest);
2288 Jump unordered = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionVS);
2289 m_assembler.csel<datasize>(dest, thenCase, elseCase, Assembler::ConditionEQ);
2290 unordered.link(this);
2291 }
2292 return;
2293 }
2294 m_assembler.csel<datasize>(dest, thenCase, elseCase, ARM64Condition(cond));
2295 }
2296
2297 template<int datasize>
2298 void moveDoubleConditionallyAfterFloatingPointCompare(DoubleCondition cond, FPRegisterID thenCase, FPRegisterID elseCase, FPRegisterID dest)
2299 {
2300 if (cond == DoubleNotEqualAndOrdered) {
2301 if (dest == thenCase) {
2302 // If the compare is unordered, elseCase is copied to thenCase and the
2303 // next fcsel has all arguments equal to elseCase.
2304 // If the compare is ordered, dest is unchanged and NE decides
2305 // what value to set.
2306 m_assembler.fcsel<datasize>(thenCase, elseCase, thenCase, Assembler::ConditionVS);
2307 m_assembler.fcsel<datasize>(dest, thenCase, elseCase, Assembler::ConditionNE);
2308 } else {
2309 m_assembler.fmov<64>(dest, elseCase);
2310 Jump unordered = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionVS);
2311 m_assembler.fcsel<datasize>(dest, thenCase, elseCase, Assembler::ConditionNE);
2312 unordered.link(this);
2313 }
2314 return;
2315 }
2316 if (cond == DoubleEqualOrUnordered) {
2317 if (dest == elseCase) {
2318 // If the compare is unordered, thenCase is copied to elseCase and the
2319 // next csel has all arguments equal to thenCase.
2320 // If the compare is ordered, dest is unchanged and EQ decides
2321 // what value to set.
2322 m_assembler.fcsel<datasize>(elseCase, thenCase, elseCase, Assembler::ConditionVS);
2323 m_assembler.fcsel<datasize>(dest, thenCase, elseCase, Assembler::ConditionEQ);
2324 } else {
2325 m_assembler.fmov<64>(dest, thenCase);
2326 Jump unordered = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionVS);
2327 m_assembler.fcsel<datasize>(dest, thenCase, elseCase, Assembler::ConditionEQ);
2328 unordered.link(this);
2329 }
2330 return;
2331 }
2332 m_assembler.fcsel<datasize>(dest, thenCase, elseCase, ARM64Condition(cond));
2333 }

2527
2528 // Stack manipulation operations:
2529 //
2530 // The ABI is assumed to provide a stack abstraction to memory,
2531 // containing machine word sized units of data. Push and pop
2532 // operations add and remove a single register sized unit of data
2533 // to or from the stack. These operations are not supported on
2534 // ARM64. Peek and poke operations read or write values on the
2535 // stack, without moving the current stack position. Additionally,
2536 // there are popToRestore and pushToSave operations, which are
2537 // designed just for quick-and-dirty saving and restoring of
2538 // temporary values. These operations don't claim to have any
2539 // ABI compatibility.
2540
2541 void pop(RegisterID) NO_RETURN_DUE_TO_CRASH
2542 {
2543 CRASH();
2544 }
2545
2546 void push(RegisterID) NO_RETURN_DUE_TO_CRASH
2547 {
2548 CRASH();
2549 }
2550
2551 void push(Address) NO_RETURN_DUE_TO_CRASH
2552 {
2553 CRASH();
2554 }
2555
2556 void push(TrustedImm32) NO_RETURN_DUE_TO_CRASH
2557 {
2558 CRASH();
2559 }
2560
2561 void popPair(RegisterID dest1, RegisterID dest2)
2562 {
2563 m_assembler.ldp<64>(dest1, dest2, ARM64Registers::sp, PairPostIndex(16));
2564 }
2565
2566 void pushPair(RegisterID src1, RegisterID src2)
2567 {
2568 m_assembler.stp<64>(src1, src2, ARM64Registers::sp, PairPreIndex(-16));
2569 }
2570
2571 void popToRestore(RegisterID dest)
2572 {
2573 m_assembler.ldr<64>(dest, ARM64Registers::sp, PostIndex(16));
2574 }
2575
2576 void pushToSave(RegisterID src)
2577 {
2578 m_assembler.str<64>(src, ARM64Registers::sp, PreIndex(-16));
2579 }
2580
2581 void pushToSaveImmediateWithoutTouchingRegisters(TrustedImm32 imm)
2582 {
2583 // We can use any non-hardware reserved register here since we restore its value.
2584 // We pick dataTempRegister arbitrarily. We don't need to invalidate it here since
2585 // we restore its original value.
2586 RegisterID reg = dataTempRegister;
2587
2588 pushPair(reg, reg);
2589 move(imm, reg);
2590 store64(reg, stackPointerRegister);
2591 load64(Address(stackPointerRegister, 8), reg);
2592 }
2593
2594 void pushToSave(Address address)
2595 {
2596 load32(address, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
2597 pushToSave(dataTempRegister);
2598 }
2599
2600 void pushToSave(TrustedImm32 imm)
2601 {
2602 move(imm, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
2603 pushToSave(dataTempRegister);
2604 }
2605
2606 void popToRestore(FPRegisterID dest)
2607 {
2608 loadDouble(stackPointerRegister, dest);
2609 add64(TrustedImm32(16), stackPointerRegister);
2610 }
2611
2612 void pushToSave(FPRegisterID src)
2613 {
2614 sub64(TrustedImm32(16), stackPointerRegister);
2615 storeDouble(src, stackPointerRegister);
2616 }
2617
2618 static constexpr ptrdiff_t pushToSaveByteOffset() { return 16; }

2620 // Register move operations:
2621
2622 void move(RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
2623 {
2624 if (src != dest)
2625 m_assembler.mov<64>(dest, src);
2626 }
2627
2628 void move(TrustedImm32 imm, RegisterID dest)
2629 {
2630 moveInternal<TrustedImm32, int32_t>(imm, dest);
2631 }
2632
2633 void move(TrustedImmPtr imm, RegisterID dest)
2634 {
2635 moveInternal<TrustedImmPtr, intptr_t>(imm, dest);
2636 }
2637
2638 void move(TrustedImm64 imm, RegisterID dest)
2639 {
2640 moveInternal<TrustedImm64, int64_t>(imm, dest);
2641 }
2642
2643 void swap(RegisterID reg1, RegisterID reg2)
2644 {
2645 move(reg1, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
2646 move(reg2, reg1);

2836 // Forwards / external control flow operations:
2837 //
2838 // This set of jump and conditional branch operations return a Jump
2839 // object which may linked at a later point, allow forwards jump,
2840 // or jumps that will require external linkage (after the code has been
2841 // relocated).
2842 //
2843 // For branches, signed <, >, <= and >= are denoted as l, g, le, and ge
2844 // respecitvely, for unsigned comparisons the names b, a, be, and ae are
2845 // used (representing the names 'below' and 'above').
2846 //
2847 // Operands to the comparision are provided in the expected order, e.g.
2848 // jle32(reg1, TrustedImm32(5)) will branch if the value held in reg1, when
2849 // treated as a signed 32bit value, is less than or equal to 5.
2850 //
2851 // jz and jnz test whether the first operand is equal to zero, and take
2852 // an optional second operand of a mask under which to perform the test.
2853
2854 Jump branch32(RelationalCondition cond, RegisterID left, RegisterID right)
2855 {
2856 m_assembler.cmp<32>(left, right);
2857 return Jump(makeBranch(cond));
2858 }
2859
2860 Jump branch32(RelationalCondition cond, RegisterID left, TrustedImm32 right)
2861 {
2862 if (!right.m_value) {
2863 if (auto resultCondition = commuteCompareToZeroIntoTest(cond))
2864 return branchTest32(*resultCondition, left, left);
2865 }
2866
2867 if (isUInt12(right.m_value))
2868 m_assembler.cmp<32>(left, UInt12(right.m_value));
2869 else if (isUInt12(-right.m_value))
2870 m_assembler.cmn<32>(left, UInt12(-right.m_value));
2871 else {
2872 moveToCachedReg(right, dataMemoryTempRegister());
2873 m_assembler.cmp<32>(left, dataTempRegister);
2874 }
2875 return Jump(makeBranch(cond));
2876 }
2877
2878 Jump branch32(RelationalCondition cond, RegisterID left, Address right)
2879 {
2880 load32(right, getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
2881 return branch32(cond, left, memoryTempRegister);
2882 }

2914 Jump branch64(RelationalCondition cond, RegisterID left, RegisterID right)
2915 {
2916 if (right == ARM64Registers::sp) {
2917 if (cond == Equal && left != ARM64Registers::sp) {
2918 // CMP can only use SP for the left argument, since we are testing for equality, the order
2919 // does not matter here.
2920 std::swap(left, right);
2921 } else {
2922 move(right, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
2923 right = dataTempRegister;
2924 }
2925 }
2926 m_assembler.cmp<64>(left, right);
2927 return Jump(makeBranch(cond));
2928 }

2960 else {

3031 void test32(RegisterID reg, TrustedImm32 mask = TrustedImm32(-1))
3032 {
3033 if (mask.m_value == -1)
3034 m_assembler.tst<32>(reg, reg);
3035 else {
3036 LogicalImmediate logicalImm = LogicalImmediate::create32(mask.m_value);
3037
3038 if (logicalImm.isValid())
3039 m_assembler.tst<32>(reg, logicalImm);
3040 else {
3041 move(mask, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3042 m_assembler.tst<32>(reg, dataTempRegister);
3043 }
3044 }

3052 Jump branchTest32(ResultCondition cond, RegisterID reg, TrustedImm32 mask = TrustedImm32(-1))
3053 {
3054 if (mask.m_value == -1) {
3055 if ((cond == Zero) || (cond == NonZero))
3056 return Jump(makeCompareAndBranch<32>(static_cast<ZeroCondition>(cond), reg));
3057 m_assembler.tst<32>(reg, reg);
3058 } else if (hasOneBitSet(mask.m_value) && ((cond == Zero) || (cond == NonZero)))
3059 return Jump(makeTestBitAndBranch(reg, getLSBSet(mask.m_value), static_cast<ZeroCondition>(cond)));
3060 else {
3061 LogicalImmediate logicalImm = LogicalImmediate::create32(mask.m_value);
3062 if (logicalImm.isValid()) {
3063 m_assembler.tst<32>(reg, logicalImm);
3064 return Jump(makeBranch(cond));
3065 }
3066
3067 move(mask, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3068 m_assembler.tst<32>(reg, dataTempRegister);
3069 }
3070 return Jump(makeBranch(cond));
3071 }

3208 // Arithmetic control flow operations:
3209 //
3210 // This set of conditional branch operations branch based
3211 // on the result of an arithmetic operation. The operation
3212 // is performed as normal, storing the result.
3213 //
3214 // * jz operations branch if the result is zero.
3215 // * jo operations branch if the (signed) arithmetic
3216 // operation caused an overflow to occur.
3217
3218 Jump branchAdd32(ResultCondition cond, RegisterID op1, RegisterID op2, RegisterID dest)
3219 {
3220 m_assembler.add<32, S>(dest, op1, op2);
3221 return Jump(makeBranch(cond));
3222 }

3224 Jump branchAdd32(ResultCondition cond, RegisterID op1, TrustedImm32 imm, RegisterID dest)
3225 {
3226 if (isUInt12(imm.m_value)) {
3227 m_assembler.add<32, S>(dest, op1, UInt12(imm.m_value));
3228 return Jump(makeBranch(cond));
3229 }
3230 if (isUInt12(-imm.m_value)) {
3231 m_assembler.sub<32, S>(dest, op1, UInt12(-imm.m_value));
3232 return Jump(makeBranch(cond));
3233 }
3234
3235 signExtend32ToPtr(imm, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3236 return branchAdd32(cond, op1, dataTempRegister, dest);
3237 }

3243 }

3255 Jump branchAdd32(ResultCondition cond, TrustedImm32 imm, AbsoluteAddress address)
3256 {
3257 load32(address.m_ptr, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3258
3259 if (isUInt12(imm.m_value)) {
3260 m_assembler.add<32, S>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(imm.m_value));
3261 store32(dataTempRegister, address.m_ptr);
3262 } else if (isUInt12(-imm.m_value)) {
3263 m_assembler.sub<32, S>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(-imm.m_value));
3264 store32(dataTempRegister, address.m_ptr);
3265 } else {
3266 move(imm, getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3267 m_assembler.add<32, S>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, memoryTempRegister);
3268 store32(dataTempRegister, address.m_ptr);
3269 }
3270
3271 return Jump(makeBranch(cond));
3272 }

3277
3278 if (isUInt12(imm.m_value))
3279 m_assembler.add<32, S>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(imm.m_value));
3280 else if (isUInt12(-imm.m_value))
3281 m_assembler.sub<32, S>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, UInt12(-imm.m_value));
3282 else {
3283 move(imm, getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3284 m_assembler.add<32, S>(dataTempRegister, dataTempRegister, memoryTempRegister);
3285 }

3287 store32(dataTempRegister, address);

3328
3329 Jump branchMul32(ResultCondition cond, RegisterID src1, RegisterID src2, RegisterID scratch1, RegisterID scratch2, RegisterID dest)
3330 {
3331 ASSERT(cond != Signed);
3332
3333 if (cond != Overflow) {
3334 m_assembler.mul<32>(dest, src1, src2);
3335 return branchTest32(cond, dest);
3336 }
3337
3338 // This is a signed multiple of two 32-bit values, producing a 64-bit result.
3339 m_assembler.smull(dest, src1, src2);
3340 // Copy bits 63..32 of the result to bits 31..0 of scratch1.
3341 m_assembler.asr<64>(scratch1, dest, 32);
3342 // Splat bit 31 of the result to bits 31..0 of scratch2.
3343 m_assembler.asr<32>(scratch2, dest, 31);
3344 // After a mul32 the top 32 bits of the register should be clear.
3345 zeroExtend32ToWord(dest, dest);
3346 // Check that bits 31..63 of the original result were all equal.
3347 return branch32(NotEqual, scratch2, scratch1);
3348 }
3349
3350 Jump branchMul32(ResultCondition cond, RegisterID src1, RegisterID src2, RegisterID dest)
3351 {
3352 return branchMul32(cond, src1, src2, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate(), getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate(), dest);
3353 }
3354
3355 Jump branchMul32(ResultCondition cond, RegisterID src, RegisterID dest)
3356 {
3357 return branchMul32(cond, dest, src, dest);
3358 }
3359
3360 Jump branchMul32(ResultCondition cond, RegisterID src, TrustedImm32 imm, RegisterID dest)
3361 {
3362 move(imm, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3363 return branchMul32(cond, dataTempRegister, src, dest);
3364 }
3365
3366 Jump branchMul64(ResultCondition cond, RegisterID src1, RegisterID src2, RegisterID scratch1, RegisterID scratch2, RegisterID dest)
3367 {
3368 ASSERT(cond != Signed);
3369
3370 // This is a signed multiple of two 64-bit values, producing a 64-bit result.
3371 m_assembler.mul<64>(dest, src1, src2);
3372
3373 if (cond != Overflow)
3374 return branchTest64(cond, dest);
3375
3376 // Compute bits 127..64 of the result into scratch1.
3377 m_assembler.smulh(scratch1, src1, src2);
3378 // Splat bit 63 of the result to bits 63..0 of scratch2.
3379 m_assembler.asr<64>(scratch2, dest, 63);
3380 // Check that bits 31..63 of the original result were all equal.
3381 return branch64(NotEqual, scratch2, scratch1);
3382 }
3383

3386 return branchMul64(cond, src1, src2, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate(), getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate(), dest);
3387 }

3492#endif
3493 }

3495 ALWAYS_INLINE Call call(PtrTag)
3496 {
3497 AssemblerLabel pointerLabel = m_assembler.label();
3498 moveWithFixedWidth(TrustedImmPtr(nullptr), getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3499 invalidateAllTempRegisters();
3500 m_assembler.blr(dataTempRegister);
3501 AssemblerLabel callLabel = m_assembler.label();
3502 ASSERT_UNUSED(pointerLabel, Assembler::getDifferenceBetweenLabels(callLabel, pointerLabel) == REPATCH_OFFSET_CALL_TO_POINTER);
3503 return Call(callLabel, Call::Linkable);
3504 }
3505

3507 {

3509 m_assembler.blr(target);
3510 return Call(m_assembler.label(), Call::None);
3511 }

3514 {

3516 return call(dataTempRegister, tag);
3517 }

3600 void compare32(RelationalCondition cond, RegisterID left, RegisterID right, RegisterID dest)
3601 {
3602 m_assembler.cmp<32>(left, right);
3603 m_assembler.cset<32>(dest, ARM64Condition(cond));
3604 }
3605
3606 void compare32(RelationalCondition cond, Address left, RegisterID right, RegisterID dest)
3607 {
3608 load32(left, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3609 m_assembler.cmp<32>(dataTempRegister, right);
3610 m_assembler.cset<32>(dest, ARM64Condition(cond));
3611 }
3612
3613 void compare32(RelationalCondition cond, RegisterID left, TrustedImm32 right, RegisterID dest)
3614 {
3615 if (!right.m_value) {
3616 if (auto resultCondition = commuteCompareToZeroIntoTest(cond)) {
3617 test32(*resultCondition, left, left, dest);
3618 return;
3619 }
3620 }
3621
3622 if (isUInt12(right.m_value))
3623 m_assembler.cmp<32>(left, UInt12(right.m_value));
3624 else if (isUInt12(-right.m_value))
3625 m_assembler.cmn<32>(left, UInt12(-right.m_value));
3626 else {
3627 move(right, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3628 m_assembler.cmp<32>(left, dataTempRegister);
3629 }
3630 m_assembler.cset<32>(dest, ARM64Condition(cond));
3631 }
3632
3633 void compare64(RelationalCondition cond, RegisterID left, RegisterID right, RegisterID dest)
3634 {
3635 m_assembler.cmp<64>(left, right);
3636 m_assembler.cset<32>(dest, ARM64Condition(cond));
3637 }
3638
3639 void compare64(RelationalCondition cond, RegisterID left, TrustedImm32 right, RegisterID dest)
3640 {
3641 if (!right.m_value) {
3642 if (auto resultCondition = commuteCompareToZeroIntoTest(cond)) {
3643 test64(*resultCondition, left, left, dest);
3644 return;
3645 }
3646 }
3647
3648 signExtend32ToPtr(right, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3649 m_assembler.cmp<64>(left, dataTempRegister);
3650 m_assembler.cset<32>(dest, ARM64Condition(cond));
3651 }
3652
3653 void compare8(RelationalCondition cond, Address left, TrustedImm32 right, RegisterID dest)
3654 {
3655 TrustedImm32 right8 = MacroAssemblerHelpers::mask8OnCondition(*this, cond, right);
3656 MacroAssemblerHelpers::load8OnCondition(*this, cond, left, getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3657 move(right8, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3658 compare32(cond, memoryTempRegister, dataTempRegister, dest);
3659 }

3661 void test32(ResultCondition cond, RegisterID src, RegisterID mask, RegisterID dest)
3662 {
3663 m_assembler.tst<32>(src, mask);
3664 m_assembler.cset<32>(dest, ARM64Condition(cond));
3665 }

3671 }

3677 }

3681 TrustedImm32 mask8 = MacroAssemblerHelpers::mask8OnCondition(*this, cond, mask);
3682 MacroAssemblerHelpers::load8OnCondition(*this, cond, address, getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3683 test32(cond, memoryTempRegister, mask8, dest);
3684 }

3688 m_assembler.tst<64>(op1, op2);
3689 m_assembler.cset<32>(dest, ARM64Condition(cond));

3692 void test64(ResultCondition cond, RegisterID src, TrustedImm32 mask, RegisterID dest)
3693 {
3694 if (mask.m_value == -1)
3695 m_assembler.tst<64>(src, src);
3696 else {
3697 signExtend32ToPtr(mask, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3698 m_assembler.tst<64>(src, dataTempRegister);
3699 }
3700 m_assembler.cset<32>(dest, ARM64Condition(cond));
3701 }

3825 ALWAYS_INLINE DataLabelPtr storePtrWithPatch(TrustedImmPtr initialValue, ImplicitAddress address)
3826 {
3827 DataLabelPtr label(this);
3828 moveWithFixedWidth(initialValue, getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
3829 store64(dataTempRegister, address);
3830 return label;
3831 }

3833 ALWAYS_INLINE DataLabelPtr storePtrWithPatch(ImplicitAddress address)
3834 {
3835 return storePtrWithPatch(TrustedImmPtr(nullptr), address);
3836 }

3839 {
3840 Assembler::setPointer(static_cast<int*>(address), value, dataTempRegister, true);

3857 // We take memoryFence to mean acqrel. This has acqrel semantics on ARM64.
3858 void memoryFence()
3859 {
3860 m_assembler.dmbISH();
3861 }
3862
3863 // We take this to mean that it prevents motion of normal stores. That's a store fence on ARM64 (hence the "ST").
3864 void storeFence()
3865 {
3866 m_assembler.dmbISHST();
3867 }
3868
3869 // We take this to mean that it prevents motion of normal loads. Ideally we'd have expressed this
3870 // using dependencies or half fences, but there are cases where this is as good as it gets. The only
3871 // way to get a standalone load fence instruction on ARM is to use the ISH fence, which is just like
3872 // the memoryFence().
3873 void loadFence()
3874 {
3875 m_assembler.dmbISH();
3876 }

4187 static std::optional<ResultCondition> commuteCompareToZeroIntoTest(RelationalCondition cond)
4188 {
4189 switch (cond) {
4190 case Equal:
4191 return Zero;
4192 case NotEqual:
4193 return NonZero;
4194 case LessThan:
4195 return Signed;
4196 case GreaterThanOrEqual:
4197 return PositiveOrZero;
4198 break;
4199 default:
4200 return std::nullopt;
4201 }
4202 }

4304 template <int dataSize>
4305 ALWAYS_INLINE Jump makeCompareAndBranch(ZeroCondition cond, RegisterID reg)
4306 {
4307 if (cond == IsZero)
4308 m_assembler.cbz<dataSize>(reg);
4309 else
4310 m_assembler.cbnz<dataSize>(reg);
4311 AssemblerLabel label = m_assembler.label();
4312 m_assembler.nop();
4313 return Jump(label, m_makeJumpPatchable ? Assembler::JumpCompareAndBranchFixedSize : Assembler::JumpCompareAndBranch, static_cast<Assembler::Condition>(cond), dataSize == 64, reg);
4314 }
4315
4316 ALWAYS_INLINE Jump makeTestBitAndBranch(RegisterID reg, unsigned bit, ZeroCondition cond)
4317 {
4318 ASSERT(bit < 64);
4319 bit &= 0x3f;
4320 if (cond == IsZero)
4321 m_assembler.tbz(reg, bit);
4322 else
4323 m_assembler.tbnz(reg, bit);
4324 AssemblerLabel label = m_assembler.label();
4325 m_assembler.nop();
4326 return Jump(label, m_makeJumpPatchable ? Assembler::JumpTestBitFixedSize : Assembler::JumpTestBit, static_cast<Assembler::Condition>(cond), bit, reg);
4327 }

4366 template<typename ImmediateType, typename rawType>
4367 void moveInternal(ImmediateType imm, RegisterID dest)
4368 {
4369 const int dataSize = sizeof(rawType) * 8;
4370 const int numberHalfWords = dataSize / 16;
4371 rawType value = bitwise_cast<rawType>(imm.m_value);
4372 uint16_t halfword[numberHalfWords];
4373
4374 // Handle 0 and ~0 here to simplify code below
4375 if (!value) {
4376 m_assembler.movz<dataSize>(dest, 0);
4377 return;
4378 }
4379 if (!~value) {
4380 m_assembler.movn<dataSize>(dest, 0);
4381 return;
4382 }
4383
4384 LogicalImmediate logicalImm = dataSize == 64 ? LogicalImmediate::create64(static_cast<uint64_t>(value)) : LogicalImmediate::create32(static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
4385
4386 if (logicalImm.isValid()) {
4387 m_assembler.movi<dataSize>(dest, logicalImm);
4388 return;
4389 }
4390
4391 // Figure out how many halfwords are 0 or FFFF, then choose movz or movn accordingly.
4392 int zeroOrNegateVote = 0;
4393 for (int i = 0; i < numberHalfWords; ++i) {
4394 halfword[i] = getHalfword(value, i);
4395 if (!halfword[i])
4396 zeroOrNegateVote++;
4397 else if (halfword[i] == 0xffff)
4398 zeroOrNegateVote--;
4399 }
4400
4401 bool needToClearRegister = true;
4402 if (zeroOrNegateVote >= 0) {
4403 for (int i = 0; i < numberHalfWords; i++) {
4404 if (halfword[i]) {
4405 if (needToClearRegister) {
4406 m_assembler.movz<dataSize>(dest, halfword[i], 16*i);
4407 needToClearRegister = false;
4408 } else
4409 m_assembler.movk<dataSize>(dest, halfword[i], 16*i);
4410 }
4411 }
4412 } else {
4413 for (int i = 0; i < numberHalfWords; i++) {
4414 if (halfword[i] != 0xffff) {
4415 if (needToClearRegister) {
4416 m_assembler.movn<dataSize>(dest, ~halfword[i], 16*i);
4417 needToClearRegister = false;
4418 } else
4419 m_assembler.movk<dataSize>(dest, halfword[i], 16*i);
4420 }
4421 }
4422 }
4423 }

4460
4461 void moveWithFixedWidth(TrustedImm32 imm, RegisterID dest)
4462 {
4463 int32_t value = imm.m_value;
4464 m_assembler.movz<32>(dest, getHalfword(value, 0));
4465 m_assembler.movk<32>(dest, getHalfword(value, 1), 16);
4466 }
4467
4468 void moveWithFixedWidth(TrustedImmPtr imm, RegisterID dest)
4469 {
4470 intptr_t value = reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(imm.m_value);
4471 m_assembler.movz<64>(dest, getHalfword(value, 0));
4472 m_assembler.movk<64>(dest, getHalfword(value, 1), 16);
4473 m_assembler.movk<64>(dest, getHalfword(value, 2), 32);
4474 if (Assembler::MAX_POINTER_BITS > 48)
4475 m_assembler.movk<64>(dest, getHalfword(value, 3), 48);
4476 }

4478 void signExtend32ToPtrWithFixedWidth(int32_t value, RegisterID dest)
4479 {
4480 if (value >= 0) {
4481 m_assembler.movz<32>(dest, getHalfword(value, 0));
4482 m_assembler.movk<32>(dest, getHalfword(value, 1), 16);
4483 } else {
4484 m_assembler.movn<32>(dest, ~getHalfword(value, 0));
4485 m_assembler.movk<32>(dest, getHalfword(value, 1), 16);
4486 }
4487 }

4489 template<int datasize>
4490 ALWAYS_INLINE void load(const void* address, RegisterID dest)
4491 {
4492 intptr_t currentRegisterContents;
4493 if (cachedMemoryTempRegister().value(currentRegisterContents)) {
4494 intptr_t addressAsInt = reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(address);
4495 intptr_t addressDelta = addressAsInt - currentRegisterContents;
4496
4497 if (dest == memoryTempRegister)
4498 cachedMemoryTempRegister().invalidate();
4499
4500 if (isInt<32>(addressDelta)) {
4501 if (Assembler::canEncodeSImmOffset(addressDelta)) {
4502 loadUnscaledImmediate<datasize>(dest, memoryTempRegister, addressDelta);
4503 return;
4504 }
4505
4506 if (Assembler::canEncodePImmOffset<datasize>(addressDelta)) {
4507 loadUnsignedImmediate<datasize>(dest, memoryTempRegister, addressDelta);
4508 return;
4509 }
4510 }
4511
4512 if ((addressAsInt & (~maskHalfWord0)) == (currentRegisterContents & (~maskHalfWord0))) {
4513 m_assembler.movk<64>(memoryTempRegister, addressAsInt & maskHalfWord0, 0);
4514 cachedMemoryTempRegister().setValue(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(address));
4515 if constexpr (datasize == 16)
4516 m_assembler.ldrh(dest, memoryTempRegister, ARM64Registers::zr);
4517 else
4518 m_assembler.ldr<datasize>(dest, memoryTempRegister, ARM64Registers::zr);
4519 return;
4520 }
4521 }
4522
4523 move(TrustedImmPtr(address), memoryTempRegister);
4524 if (dest == memoryTempRegister)
4525 cachedMemoryTempRegister().invalidate();
4526 else
4527 cachedMemoryTempRegister().setValue(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(address));
4528 if constexpr (datasize == 16)
4529 m_assembler.ldrh(dest, memoryTempRegister, ARM64Registers::zr);
4530 else
4531 m_assembler.ldr<datasize>(dest, memoryTempRegister, ARM64Registers::zr);
4532 }
4533
4534 template<int datasize>
4535 ALWAYS_INLINE void store(RegisterID src, const void* address)
4536 {
4537 ASSERT(src != memoryTempRegister);
4538 intptr_t currentRegisterContents;
4539 if (cachedMemoryTempRegister().value(currentRegisterContents)) {
4540 intptr_t addressAsInt = reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(address);
4541 intptr_t addressDelta = addressAsInt - currentRegisterContents;
4542
4543 if (isInt<32>(addressDelta)) {
4544 if (Assembler::canEncodeSImmOffset(addressDelta)) {
4545 storeUnscaledImmediate<datasize>(src, memoryTempRegister, addressDelta);
4546 return;
4547 }
4548
4549 if (Assembler::canEncodePImmOffset<datasize>(addressDelta)) {
4550 storeUnsignedImmediate<datasize>(src, memoryTempRegister, addressDelta);
4551 return;
4552 }
4553 }
4554
4555 if ((addressAsInt & (~maskHalfWord0)) == (currentRegisterContents & (~maskHalfWord0))) {
4556 m_assembler.movk<64>(memoryTempRegister, addressAsInt & maskHalfWord0, 0);
4557 cachedMemoryTempRegister().setValue(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(address));
4558 if constexpr (datasize == 16)
4559 m_assembler.strh(src, memoryTempRegister, ARM64Registers::zr);
4560 else
4561 m_assembler.str<datasize>(src, memoryTempRegister, ARM64Registers::zr);
4562 return;
4563 }
4564 }
4565
4566 move(TrustedImmPtr(address), memoryTempRegister);
4567 cachedMemoryTempRegister().setValue(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(address));
4568 if constexpr (datasize == 16)
4569 m_assembler.strh(src, memoryTempRegister, ARM64Registers::zr);
4570 else
4571 m_assembler.str<datasize>(src, memoryTempRegister, ARM64Registers::zr);
4572 }

4574 template <int dataSize>
4575 ALWAYS_INLINE bool tryMoveUsingCacheRegisterContents(intptr_t immediate, CachedTempRegister& dest)
4576 {
4577 intptr_t currentRegisterContents;
4578 if (dest.value(currentRegisterContents)) {
4579 if (currentRegisterContents == immediate)
4580 return true;
4581
4582 LogicalImmediate logicalImm = dataSize == 64 ? LogicalImmediate::create64(static_cast<uint64_t>(immediate)) : LogicalImmediate::create32(static_cast<uint32_t>(immediate));
4583
4584 if (logicalImm.isValid()) {
4585 m_assembler.movi<dataSize>(dest.registerIDNoInvalidate(), logicalImm);
4586 dest.setValue(immediate);
4587 return true;
4588 }
4589
4590 if ((immediate & maskUpperWord) == (currentRegisterContents & maskUpperWord)) {
4591 if ((immediate & maskHalfWord1) != (currentRegisterContents & maskHalfWord1))
4592 m_assembler.movk<dataSize>(dest.registerIDNoInvalidate(), (immediate & maskHalfWord1) >> 16, 16);
4593
4594 if ((immediate & maskHalfWord0) != (currentRegisterContents & maskHalfWord0))
4595 m_assembler.movk<dataSize>(dest.registerIDNoInvalidate(), immediate & maskHalfWord0, 0);
4596
4597 dest.setValue(immediate);
4598 return true;
4599 }
4600 }
4601
4602 return false;
4603 }
4604
4605 void moveToCachedReg(TrustedImm32 imm, CachedTempRegister& dest)
4606 {
4607 if (tryMoveUsingCacheRegisterContents<32>(static_cast<intptr_t>(imm.m_value), dest))
4608 return;
4609
4610 moveInternal<TrustedImm32, int32_t>(imm, dest.registerIDNoInvalidate());
4611 dest.setValue(imm.m_value);
4612 }
4613
4614 void moveToCachedReg(TrustedImmPtr imm, CachedTempRegister& dest)
4615 {
4616 if (tryMoveUsingCacheRegisterContents<64>(imm.asIntptr(), dest))
4617 return;
4618
4619 moveInternal<TrustedImmPtr, intptr_t>(imm, dest.registerIDNoInvalidate());
4620 dest.setValue(imm.asIntptr());
4621 }
4622
4623 void moveToCachedReg(TrustedImm64 imm, CachedTempRegister& dest)

4626 return;
4627
4628 moveInternal<TrustedImm64, int64_t>(imm, dest.registerIDNoInvalidate());

4630 }

4743 template<int datasize>
4744 void atomicStrongCAS(StatusCondition cond, RegisterID expectedAndResult, RegisterID newValue, Address address, RegisterID result)
4745 {
4746 zeroExtend<datasize>(expectedAndResult, expectedAndResult);
4747
4748 RegisterID simpleAddress = extractSimpleAddress(address);
4749 RegisterID tmp = getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate();
4750
4751 Label reloop = label();
4752 loadLinkAcq<datasize>(simpleAddress, tmp);
4753 Jump failure = branch<datasize>(NotEqual, expectedAndResult, tmp);
4754
4755 storeCondRel<datasize>(newValue, simpleAddress, result);
4756 branchTest32(NonZero, result).linkTo(reloop, this);
4757 move(TrustedImm32(cond == Success), result);
4758 Jump done = jump();
4759
4760 failure.link(this);
4761 move(tmp, expectedAndResult);
4762 storeCondRel<datasize>(tmp, simpleAddress, result);
4763 branchTest32(NonZero, result).linkTo(reloop, this);
4764 move(TrustedImm32(cond == Failure), result);
4765
4766 done.link(this);
4767 }

4769 template<int datasize, typename AddressType>
4770 void atomicRelaxedStrongCAS(StatusCondition cond, RegisterID expectedAndResult, RegisterID newValue, AddressType address, RegisterID result)
4771 {
4772 zeroExtend<datasize>(expectedAndResult, expectedAndResult);
4773
4774 RegisterID simpleAddress = extractSimpleAddress(address);
4775 RegisterID tmp = getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate();
4776
4777 Label reloop = label();
4778 loadLink<datasize>(simpleAddress, tmp);
4779 Jump failure = branch<datasize>(NotEqual, expectedAndResult, tmp);
4780
4781 storeCond<datasize>(newValue, simpleAddress, result);
4782 branchTest32(NonZero, result).linkTo(reloop, this);
4783 move(TrustedImm32(cond == Success), result);
4784 Jump done = jump();
4785
4786 failure.link(this);
4787 move(tmp, expectedAndResult);
4788 move(TrustedImm32(cond == Failure), result);
4789
4790 done.link(this);
4791 }

4793 template<int datasize, typename AddressType>
4794 JumpList branchAtomicWeakCAS(StatusCondition cond, RegisterID expectedAndClobbered, RegisterID newValue, AddressType address)
4795 {
4796 zeroExtend<datasize>(expectedAndClobbered, expectedAndClobbered);
4797
4798 RegisterID simpleAddress = extractSimpleAddress(address);
4799 RegisterID tmp = getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate();
4800
4801 JumpList success;
4802 JumpList failure;
4803
4804 loadLinkAcq<datasize>(simpleAddress, tmp);
4805 failure.append(branch<datasize>(NotEqual, expectedAndClobbered, tmp));
4806 storeCondRel<datasize>(newValue, simpleAddress, expectedAndClobbered);
4807
4808 switch (cond) {
4809 case Success:
4810 success.append(branchTest32(Zero, expectedAndClobbered));
4811 failure.link(this);
4812 return success;
4813 case Failure:
4814 failure.append(branchTest32(NonZero, expectedAndClobbered));
4815 return failure;
4816 }
4817
4818 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4819 }
4820
4821 template<int datasize, typename AddressType>
4822 JumpList branchAtomicRelaxedWeakCAS(StatusCondition cond, RegisterID expectedAndClobbered, RegisterID newValue, AddressType address)
4823 {
4824 zeroExtend<datasize>(expectedAndClobbered, expectedAndClobbered);
4825
4826 RegisterID simpleAddress = extractSimpleAddress(address);
4827 RegisterID tmp = getCachedDataTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate();
4828

4830 JumpList failure;
4831

4833 failure.append(branch<datasize>(NotEqual, expectedAndClobbered, tmp));
4834 storeCond<datasize>(newValue, simpleAddress, expectedAndClobbered);
4835
4836 switch (cond) {
4837 case Success:
4838 success.append(branchTest32(Zero, expectedAndClobbered));
4839 failure.link(this);
4840 return success;
4841 case Failure:
4842 failure.append(branchTest32(NonZero, expectedAndClobbered));
4843 return failure;
4844 }

4846 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4847 }
4848
4849 RegisterID extractSimpleAddress(ImplicitAddress address)
4850 {
4851 if (!address.offset)
4852 return address.base;
4853
4854 signExtend32ToPtr(TrustedImm32(address.offset), getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate());
4855 add64(address.base, memoryTempRegister);
4856 return memoryTempRegister;
4857 }
4858
4859 // This uses both the memory and data temp, but only returns the memorty temp. So you can use the
4860 // data temp after this finishes.
4861 RegisterID extractSimpleAddress(BaseIndex address)
4862 {
4863 RegisterID result = getCachedMemoryTempRegisterIDAndInvalidate();
4864 lshift64(address.index, TrustedImm32(address.scale), result);
4865 add64(address.base, result);
4866 add64(TrustedImm32(address.offset), result);
4867 return result;
4868 }
4869
4870 Jump jumpAfterFloatingPointCompare(DoubleCondition cond)
4871 {
4872 if (cond == DoubleNotEqualAndOrdered) {
4873 // ConditionNE jumps if NotEqual *or* unordered - force the unordered cases not to jump.
4874 Jump unordered = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionVS);
4875 Jump result = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionNE);
4876 unordered.link(this);
4877 return result;
4878 }
4879 if (cond == DoubleEqualOrUnordered) {
4880 Jump unordered = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionVS);
4881 Jump notEqual = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionNE);
4882 unordered.link(this);
4883 // We get here if either unordered or equal.
4884 Jump result = jump();
4885 notEqual.link(this);
4886 return result;
4887 }
4888 return makeBranch(cond);
4889 }
4890
4891 template<typename Function>
4892 void floatingPointCompare(DoubleCondition cond, FPRegisterID left, FPRegisterID right, RegisterID dest, Function compare)
4893 {
4894 if (cond == DoubleNotEqualAndOrdered) {
4895 // ConditionNE sets 1 if NotEqual *or* unordered - force the unordered cases not to set 1.
4896 move(TrustedImm32(0), dest);
4897 compare(left, right);
4898 Jump unordered = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionVS);
4899 m_assembler.cset<32>(dest, Assembler::ConditionNE);
4900 unordered.link(this);
4901 return;
4902 }
4903 if (cond == DoubleEqualOrUnordered) {
4904 // ConditionEQ sets 1 only if Equal - force the unordered cases to set 1 too.
4905 move(TrustedImm32(1), dest);
4906 compare(left, right);
4907 Jump unordered = makeBranch(Assembler::ConditionVS);
4908 m_assembler.cset<32>(dest, Assembler::ConditionEQ);
4909 unordered.link(this);
4910 return;
4911 }
4912 compare(left, right);
4913 m_assembler.cset<32>(dest, ARM64Condition(cond));
4914 }

4918 template<PtrTag tag>
4919 static void linkCall(void* code, Call call, FunctionPtr<tag> function)
4920 {
4921 if (!call.isFlagSet(Call::Near))
4922 Assembler::linkPointer(code, call.m_label.labelAtOffset(REPATCH_OFFSET_CALL_TO_POINTER), function.executableAddress());
4923 else if (call.isFlagSet(Call::Tail))
4924 Assembler::linkJump(code, call.m_label, function.template retaggedExecutableAddress<NoPtrTag>());
4925 else
4926 Assembler::linkCall(code, call.m_label, function.template retaggedExecutableAddress<NoPtrTag>());
4927 }
